# Keycloak image exceptions
#
# Policy basis:
# - Block HIGH/CRITICAL findings that have a fixed version
# - Allow explicit exceptions when the reported fix path is not actionable for
#   the consumed upstream image or appears to be scanner/version-range noise
#
# These exceptions are intentionally narrow and should be revisited whenever the
# base Keycloak image or bundled dependencies change.

# Reported against jackson-core 2.19.2 with inconsistent fixed-version guidance
# (includes 2.18.6 as "fixed"), indicating scanner advisory ambiguity rather
# than a clear actionable upgrade path inside the upstream Keycloak bundle.
GHSA-72hv-8253-57qq

# Reported against bundled mssql-jdbc 13.2.1 with a non-actionable fixed list
# for this upstream image context. The deployment uses PostgreSQL, not SQL
# Server, so this remains documented but excepted from the blocking gate.
CVE-2025-59250
